          "None Specified",
          "[DBoard, Col-Exp, Resource, Video, MCQ, VMCQ, Exercise, Self-Efficacy, Intrinsic Motivation, Test Anxiety, Positive Self-Regulated Strategy Use, Negative Self-Regulated Use]",
          "Initial exploration of the data was done using PCA with Varimax rotation. Questionaire consistency was evaluated using Cronbach alpha. ",
          "Hierarchical Clustering",
          " - ",
          "2",
          "High self-regulated and high-achieving (n=62)\n\nThese students tend to exhibit the best indicators when it comes to SRL and interaction patterns. These students also exhibit the highest grades overall.\n\nLow self-regulated and low-achieving students (n=83)\n\nLowest patterns of interaction and lowest values on the SRL constucts - leading also to the lowest grade.",
          "Constructs and variables usually associated with engative performance have, in this study, effectively led to worst results. \n\nThere is value in combining different sources of variables as it allows for a more fine-grained evaluation of student behavior and their SRL perceptions.",
          "Authors do Hierarchical clustering to perform to identify 2 groups of students.  Results are consistent with literature.",
          "Survey was made for the course as a whole, not dividing betwen face-to-face and online components. \n\nSRL is dynamic so capturing some idea at one point may not fully translate into a complete experience throughout the course. "
        ],
